<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-29T19:33:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-02T14:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>On April 16, Secretary Acheson testified before the Senate Foreign
                                Relations Committee that the threat of famine in India was
                                immediate, and he urged passage of S. 872, the bill before the
                                committee. See the text of the Secretary’s statement in Department
                                of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, April 23, 1951, page
                                674.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>